    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_ProcessData",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to process billing data within a specific billing period. It performs several operations, including executing other stored procedures, updating records, and handling errors. The procedure is part of a batch processing system, used for financial or utility billing purposes. It interacts with tables and procedures within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Batch",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " and "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "NYPA",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schemas, indicating a structured approach to managing data processing tasks."
        }
